title: Volleyball: Centennial advances in 8-8A
text:
Previous Next 
Erin Ergle had seven points and 15 assists Monday as St. Lucie West Centennial High School’s volleyball team defeated Treasure Coast 25-14, 25-16, 25-19 in the first round of the District 8-8A tournament at Centennial. 
Ayannah Henry added 10 kills, five service points and four aces for Centennial (6-8). 
Chloe Villacastin had six kills and six service points, Kenzie Waldkoetter had eight digs, Sydney Oglesby had six kills and Cameron Pagan finished with six service points and two aces. 
Kayla Zaffrullah had 25 digs and Yasmin White had 12 attacks for Treasure Coast (5-17). 
Centennial hosts top-seeded Martin County in a district semifinal at 7 p.m. Tuesday. 
DISTRICT 15-5A 
Port St. Lucie d. Fort Pierce Westwood, 25-10, 25-19, 25-19: The Jaguars (4-9) won a first-round match at Port St. Lucie. 
Port St. Lucie meets top-seeded Suncoast in a district semifinal at 5 p.m. Tuesday at John Carroll Catholic. 
DISTRICT 11-3A 
St. Edward’s d. FAU High, 25-5, 25-8, 25-11: Olivia Oriaku had seven kills, seven aces, two blocks and 14 service points as the Pirates advanced to a district semifinal. 
Emily Hudson added 22 assists and two kills for St. Edward’s (13-9). Angela Schwerer had 14 service points, three kills and three aces. 
Nicole Alden had three kills and four aces. Caroline Campione had five kills. 
St. Edward’s plays at 7 p.m. Tuesday at second-seeded Jupiter Christian in a district semifinal. 
DISTRICT 11-2A 
The Pine School d. Master’s Academy, 25-19, 25-14, 25-18: Ali Denney had 15 kills, 28 digs and nine aces as the Knights advanced to the district semifinals. 
Melissa Coolidge added 19 assists and seven aces for Pine School (20-5). 
Chloe Munson had 10 digs. 
Pine School hosts third-seeded Covenant Christian in a district semifinal at 7 p.m. Tuesday. 
Brevard HEAT d. Community Christian: 25-18, 25-12, 25-8: The Cougars lost a first-round match in Melbourne. 
Covenant Christian d. Morningside Academy, 25-10, 25-16, 25-12: The Eagles lost a first-round match in Palm Bay.
